						<summary>

						<p>This belongs to the 5th year of Tribhuvana-chakravartin <hi rend="bold">Vikrama-Pāṇḍyadēva.</hi> It is mutilated at the right end and seems to record a gift of land for forming a flowergarden for the temple by one Tiruviḍaimaruduḍaiyāṉ a horse dealer of Malai-Maṇḍalam.</p>						

